food. most travellers to india will become at least slightly ill during their stay there - even indians returning from abroad can become ill as their bodies readjust to the food, bugs, climate and sanitation conditions. however, with precautions the chance and severity of any illness can be minimized. don't stress yourself too much at the beginning of your journey to allow your body to acclimatize to the country. for example, take a day of rest upon arrival, at least on your first visit. many travellers get ill for wanting to do too much in too little time. be careful 